{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Tables","slug":"css-tables","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"12 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Borders","CSS Padding"],"learning_objectives":["Style table borders","Collapse table borders","Style table width and height","Text alignment in tables","Create zebra-striped tables"],"theory":"CSS greatly improves the look of HTML tables.\n\n*   `border`: Specifies borders for tables, rows, and cells.\n*   `border-collapse`: Whether table borders should be collapsed into a single border or detached.\n*   `text-align` & `vertical-align`: Aligns text within cells.\n*   `padding`: Adds space inside cells.","syntax":"table {\n  border-collapse: collapse;\n  width: 100%;\n}\n\nth, td {\n  border: 1px solid #ddd;\n  padding: 8px;\n  text-align: left;\n}","examples":[{"code":"tr:nth-child(even) {background-color: #f2f2f2;}","output":"Every even row has a grey background.","explanation":"Creates a 'Zebra Striped' table for better readability of large datasets."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Double borders","correction":"By default, tables have separate borders for the table and cells. Use `border-collapse: collapse` to fix this.","example":""}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"What is the difference between border-collapse: separate and collapse?","answer":"Separate (default) keeps space between cell borders. Collapse merges them into one single border.","difficulty":"Medium"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Center text in all table headers <th>.","hint":"text-align property.","solution":"th { text-align: center; }","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Data Dashboards","description":"Financial and Admin dashboards rely heavily on clean, well-spaced, striped tables to present data.","code":"th { background-color: #04AA6D; color: white; }"}],"exam_notes":["border-spacing only works when border-collapse is separate.","caption-side puts the table caption top or botto